<!-- Website -->
A collection of webpages is known as a Website.

A website has three parts: -
    Frontend - The content that are visible to the end user.
    Browser Scripting - Browser send some script like Alert box and all
    Backend - A program through which the website works but can not be accessed by a user.

<!-- Syllabus -->

    HTML 
<!-- RAW DATA -->
    CSS
<!-- Design & Feel -->
    BOOTSTRAP
<!-- Third Party CSS -->
    MEDIAQUERY
<!-- Align everything according to the screen size-->
    JAVASCRIPT
<!-- Scripting Work (alert box, dark light mode) -->
    PHP
<!-- Login Logout (Authentication & Authorization) -->
    SQL
<!-- Backend -->

HTML - Hypertext Markup Language
    Hypertext > It refers to the way in which web pages are linked together.
    Markup > Sequencing or well defined & well structured

IDE - Integrated Development Environment

<!-- Software where we can use for web development (Text editors). -->
Sublime 
Atom
Notepad
Notepad++
Visual Studio Code (Suggested)
etc..

HTML
> Hypertext Markup Language
> Helps to create our own website.
> Connect a series of web pages
> Creates an Interaction with Browser
> .html > Extension

CSS
> Cascading Style Sheet
> GIves a look and makes a design for our website.

Design 
> Inline CSS - In Tagname
> Style Tag / Internal CSS / Embeeded CSS - CSS in Head Tag (<head>)
> Style Sheet / External CSS - Css in a different file.


<!-- Paired Tag -->
<head>Content</head> 
<body></body>
<h1></h1>
<html></html>

<!-- Empty Tag -->
<br> > Break
<hr> > Horizontal Ray

<!-- Attributes -->
<a></a>
<img></img>
alt
title
style
    <!-- Inline CSS -->
    <tagname(p, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, span, etc...) style="property:value">
        <h1 style="color:blue">
    
    <!-- Internal CSS -->
    <head>
        <style>
            .
            #
        </style>
    </head>

    <!-- External CSS -->
        New Stylesheet (.css file)

Formatting
    <b></b> (bold)
        <strong></strong> (bold)
    <i></i> (italic)
        <em></em>(emphasized / italic)
    <mark></mark>
    <small></small>
    <sub></sub> (subscript)
    <sup></sup> (superscript)
    <center></center>
    <del></del>
    <ins></ins>

Quotations
    <cite></cite> // Images Caption / Italic
    <address></address> // Defines the address
    <abbr></abbr> // title
    <blockquote></blockquote> // third party writings

